## 2026-04-03 - Server generator routes reject valid shadowScale type and root-metadata rollback is broken
- Added `'shadowScale'` to `VALID_GENERATOR_TYPES` array in `routes/generators.ts` (was missing, causing 400 on POST/PUT for shadow scale generators). Also added `ShadowScaleConfig` import and a full `shadowScale` case in `validateGeneratorConfig` that validates `color` (string) and `steps` (Array<{name, offsetX, offsetY, blur, spread, opacity}>).
- Fixed the `snapshotGroup(..., '__root__')` sentinel in `routes/tokens.ts` PATCH `/tokens/:set/groups/meta`. When `groupPath` is empty (root-level metadata update), `snapshotGroup` with `'__root__'` matched no real token paths, producing an empty snapshot and making the operation non-rollbackable. Fix: use `snapshotSet` when `groupPath` is empty, `snapshotGroup` otherwise.
- Files changed: `packages/server/src/routes/generators.ts` ~L14 (import), ~L24 (VALID_GENERATOR_TYPES), ~L216 (shadowScale case in validateGeneratorConfig); `packages/server/src/routes/tokens.ts` ~L269 (snapshotGroup → snapshotSet for root)

