## 2026-04-03 - Core DTCG resolver loadSource has no cycle detection for internal $ref pointers
- Added a `visited: Set<string>` parameter (default `new Set()`) to the `loadSource` function. When an internal `#/` pointer is encountered, the function checks if `ref` is already in `visited` — if so, it logs a warning with the full cycle path and returns an empty Map. Otherwise it creates a new child set (`new Set(visited).add(ref)`) and passes it to all recursive `loadSource` calls within the referenced set's sources.
- Files changed: `packages/core/src/dtcg-resolver.ts` ~L239-289
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

