## 2026-04-03 - Server `renameSet` multi-step file mutation has a crash-unsafe window and silent rollback
- Added crash-recovery marker pattern to `renameSet`: writes `$rename-pending.json` (containing `{oldName, newName}`) before touching any files, then removes it after both steps complete. A crash between file rename and themes update is now recoverable on next startup.
- Added `recoverPendingRename()` called during `initialize()`: reads the marker, checks which step completed (by testing file existence), and re-applies the themes update if needed. Handles four cases: rename incomplete (clean up marker), rename done/themes not done (reapply themes + cleanup), both files exist (ambiguous — log error, leave marker), neither file exists (stale marker cleanup).
- Extracted `applyThemesRename(oldName, newName)` as a private helper — used by both `renameSet` and `recoverPendingRename`, eliminating inline duplication.

